addr="nt-002P"
title="Galois extension and Galois group">Galois</fr:link> extension, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G=\mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)\in \mathbb {F}[x]]]></fr:tex> be an irreducible polynomial. If there exists some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(\alpha )=0]]></fr:tex>, then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[f(x)=\prod _{\beta \in  G\alpha }(x-\beta ),]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G\alpha =\{g\alpha \mid  g\in  G\}]]></fr:tex> is the set of <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0032.xml"
addr="nt-0032"
title="Galois Conjugate">Galois conjugates</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>. In particular, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0025.xml"
addr="nt-0025"
title="Separable Polynomial">separable</fr:link> and splits over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
